      "id": "spine_medicine_clinical_l4_brachial_plexus_injuries_core_principles",
      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_medicine_clinical_l3_brachial_plexus_injuries",
      "content": {
        "title": "Brachial Plexus Injuries — Trauma and Reconstruction — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Traumatic or obstetric injury to the brachial plexus nerve roots and trunks causing upper extremity weakness, sensory loss, and dysfunction.",
        "summary": "Erb-Duchenne and Klumpke patterns localize injury. Repair, grafting, and nerve transfer restore function when reinnervation is limited. Sunderland classification guides prognosis."
      },
      "knowledge_graph": {
